  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nTokio panics during sync. \r\n\r\n## Version\r\n\r\n- Lighthouse/v0.2.13-32338bca\r\n\r\n## Present Behaviour\r\n\r\nStarting fresh on this build without prior DB, on --testnet medalla, eventually tokio panics:\r\n\r\n```\r\nbeacon_1            | Oct 03 14:33:50.023 INFO Syncing                                 est_time: 11 hrs 9 mins, speed: 10.66 slots/sec, distance: 428180 slots (8 weeks 3 days), peers: 3, service: slot_notifier\r\nbeacon_1            | thread 'tokio-runtime-worker' panicked at 'internal error: entered unreachable code: Add block for batch in wrong state: AwaitingProcessing(16Uiu2HAm4GPgBiju2ZLp9D4MmBphqMZd12oAa3eGzCrrCEbrfvSG, 222 blocks)', /rustc/04488afe34512aa4c33566eb16d8c912a3ae04f9/src/libstd/macros.rs:16:9\r\nbeacon_1            | note: run with `RUST_BACKTRACE=1` environment variable to display a backtrace\r\nbeacon_1            | Oct 03 14:33:56.597 WARN Could not send message to the sync service, error: channel closed\r\n```\r\n\r\nRestarting the beacon will get it to sync again for a little while, before panic repeats at a point further into the chain.\r\n\r\n",
